title: Appointments to Council on Human Reproductive Technology
content_text:
p>
	The Government today (April 17) announced the re-appointment of Ms Lisa Yip 
	Sau-wah as the Deputy Chairperson of the Council on Human Reproductive 
	Technology. Members Mr Herman Hu Shao-ming and Professor Agnes Tiwari Fung-yee 
	were also re-appointed. The appointments will take effect from May 11, 2014, 
	for a term of three years. Established in 2001 under the Human Reproductive Technology Ordinance, the 
	Council on Human Reproductive Technology is tasked with regulating the

Council on Human Reproductive Technology is tasked with regulating the 
	conduct of reproductive technology including embryo research in Hong Kong 
	through a licensing system and the publication of a code of practice for the 
	relevant professions. Under section 4(2) of the Ordinance, the Council consists of 26 members from 
	a wide range of disciplines, including medical specialists, legal 
	professionals, a social worker, a scholar in philosophy and ethics, a 
	psychologist, a sociologist, local community leaders and government

psychologist, a sociologist, local community leaders and government representatives. The membership list of the Council with effect from May 11, 2014, is as follows: Mr Gregory Leung Wing-lup (Chairperson)
